This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for predicting event descriptions from preceding sentences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the model, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses BLEU score as a metric, which is commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning (cs.NE).
